comment.body:
@papb I am working on the issue and I have two questions:

1) I have started the database containers using `docker-compose up postgres-95 mysql-57 mssql` but the tests are failing for mariadb. Contributing.md does not suggest any username or password for the database. 

![Snip20190908_8](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31940639/64496102-5f55f500-d256-11e9-9ab2-d724b837f1a9.png)

2) I have added support for multiple key attributes using a string[] as shown in the screenshot below. Do you expect any other format for the names of the primaryKeyAttributes?

![Snip20190908_7](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31940639/64496056-ed7dab80-d255-11e9-8909-a7ddef4a57a6.png)


If everything is done right then I will make a commit to the branch with the following commit message and open a PR. Thanks for your attention.  
 ```
feat: Added support for multiple primary key attributes

Added support for multiple primary key attributes in sequelize/types/lib/model.d.ts

Closes #11392
```
